		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well my theory (which would be backed up by the majority of readers) would be much more feasible than yours.
<br />
<br />Let's go w/ a nice round number for the transfer rate for the time, say...300 baud.  Now let's say you have an NROM-based famicom title w/ an 8KB CHR-ROM &amp; 16KB PRG-ROM.  It would take over 1 1/3 minutes to load.  This would also mean that Nintendo  would have to put an additional 8KB of RAM into the unit so the PPU can directly access CHR data.  Which seems more profitable:  extra RAM &amp; the loss of at least 20% of the market tired of waiting, or a 60ish pin connector (assuming no EXP pins)?
<br />
<br />EDIT:  Also cassettes can be copied much easier than a Famicom cart.

		

		</td>
