 it was used for.  </div>
<br />I'm pulling it out of my ass? The AVS keyboard/cassette even have the same layout as the Family BASIC keyboard/cassette! Nintendo always reused unmodified Famicom software when they brought hardware to the NES. If they brought over the Family BASIC keyboard (which is literally called the Family *BASIC* Keyboard) they would have used the software it was intended for: BASIC! AVS was additionally going to be marketted as an inexpensive home computer, which at the time meant.... BASIC! 
<br />
<br />Yes, this is speculation, but all speculations aren't equal! Since my speculation is the common speculation, you should be defending your speculation, not me. I suggest you go to the Nintendo World Store and prove that the device hasn't a cartridge slot and they never planned one.

		

