		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I just wanted to point out that there's no cables on those controllers.  Or anything.  I say no electronics in there.  In fact, I say the actual proto is in NOJ headquarters somewhere, and that display was a spare set of molds they had.
<br />
<br />Anyway, magnetic tape is still used by pretty much every company nowadays for backup.  Sure, some will use hard drives, but those are small companies.  When you canhold multiple terabytes per tape, you can't beat the price and size.
